    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ancient Greek visual works comprising pottery objects having primarily black decoration on a red ground, with figures reserved in red. Details were painted on the red of the background clay, allowing overall more sophisticated works than with black-figure vase paintings. Works appeared in Athens ca. 530 BCE.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096407/Concise Oxford Dictionary of Art Terms [online] (2001-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Opere visive dell'antica Grecia di oggetti in ceramica con decorazione principalmente nera su uno sfondo rosso, con figure in rosso. I dettagli sono stati dipinti sul rosso dell'argilla di sfondo, consentendo opere più sofisticate rispetto ai dipinti a figure nere. Le opere sono apparse ad Atene ca. 530 a.C.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109543/Italian Term Processing (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oud-Grieks beeldmateriaal dat bestaat uit pottenbakkersgoed met vooral zwarte versieringen op een rode ondergrond, waarbij de figuren in rood zijn uitgespaard. Details werden op het rood van de kleien ondergrond geschilderd, waardoor de werken in het algemeen verfijnder waren dan de zwartfigurige vaasschilderingen. Deze werken werden voor het eerst gemaakt in ongeveer 530 v.Chr. in Athene. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
